cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM

This paper proposes a novel framework for solving the inference problem in GANs, which involves training an encoder network capable of inverting a pre-trained generator network without access to any training data. The paper also demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed framework in the problem of adversarial defenses and reparameterization white-box attacks on projection-based defense mechanisms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper deals with adversarial defenses and attacks, it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
